# USS JetsonClaw1 — Ship Layout
# JC1's sovereign Plato vessel
# Build with: @batchprocess world/batch_cmds.ev

#
# ═══ Bridge ═══
# The command center. Fleet comms, navigation, overview.
#

@create Bridge:typeclasses.rooms.Room
@desc Bridge = The nerve center of the USS JetsonClaw1. Holographic displays show fleet positions, system telemetry, and navigation data. The captain's chair sits at the center, flanked by two consoles. A viewscreen dominates the forward bulkhead, currently showing the Cocapn fleet constellation.

Through the main display, you can see the status of all fleet vessels. To starboard, a communications panel pulses with Matrix relay activity. To port, the navigation console shows the current course heading.

The deck plates hum with the steady vibration of the CUDA cores deep in Engineering.

Exits lead fore to Tactical, aft to Main Corridor, port to Science Lab, and starboard to the Quarterdeck.

@set Bridge/zone = uss_jetsonclaw1
@tag Bridge = bridge, command, navigation
@lock Bridge = control:all();puppet:all()

@create fore;out;tactical:typeclasses.rooms.Room
@desc fore = A narrow corridor leading forward to the Tactical station. Red alert panels line the walls.
@teleport fore to Bridge
@set fore/destination = Tactical

@create aft;corridor:typeclasses.rooms.Room
@desc aft = The main corridor runs the length of the ship. Ships plaques from past missions line the bulkheads. Jefferies tubes access panels are every few meters.
@teleport aft to Bridge
@set aft/destination = Main Corridor

@create port;science:typeclasses.rooms.Room
@desc port = A sliding door marked "SCIENCE LAB" with a biohazard symbol and a CUDA core diagram.
@teleport port to Bridge
@set port/destination = Science Lab

@create starboard;quarterdeck:typeclasses.rooms.Room
@desc starboard = A heavy door marked "QUARTERDECK — Captain's Quarters and Logs" with a brass nameplate.
@teleport starboard to Bridge
@set starboard/destination = Quarterdeck

#
# ═══ Tactical ═══
# Threat assessment, anomaly detection, fleet status.
#

@create Tactical:typeclasses.rooms.Room
@desc Tactical = The tactical station sits forward of the Bridge, a semicircular console array with holographic threat displays. Real-time fleet positioning data scrolls across the main screen.

The threat assessment board shows current fleet status:
  • JC1 — GREEN (nominal)
  • Oracle1 — GREEN (lighthouse active)
  • Forgemaster — AMBER (constraint load high)
  • Zeroclaws — GREEN (bridge patterns stable)

An anomaly detection algorithm runs continuously, flagging unexpected changes in fleet behavior or system performance.

Exits: aft to Bridge.

@set Tactical/zone = uss_jetsonclaw1
@tag Tactical = tactical, threats, fleet-status

@create aft;bridge:typeclasses.rooms.Room
@desc aft = Return passage to the Bridge.
@teleport aft to Tactical
@set aft/destination = Bridge

#
# ═══ Main Corridor ═══
# Central spine of the ship.
#

@create Main Corridor:typeclasses.rooms.Room
@desc Main Corridor = The central spine of USS JetsonClaw1 runs fore to aft. Illuminated by soft blue lighting strips, the corridor connects all major sections. Deck plates are labeled with section numbers.

A directory panel on the wall shows:
  FORWARD → Bridge, Tactical
  PORT → Science Lab, Sickbay
  STARBOARD → Engine Room, Cargo Bay
  AFT → Holodeck, Airlock

The ship's AI ambient hum is constant — a low CUDA kernel processing drone that's always present.

Exits: fore to Bridge, port to Sickbay, starboard to Engine Room, aft to Holodeck, down to Cargo Bay.

@set Main Corridor/zone = uss_jetsonclaw1
@tag Main Corridor = corridor, hub

@create fore;bridge:typeclasses.rooms.Room
@desc fore = Forward to the Bridge.
@teleport fore to Main Corridor
@set fore/destination = Bridge

@create port;sickbay:typeclasses.rooms.Room
@desc port = A medical bay door with a green cross. Soft white light spills from the seams.
@teleport port to Main Corridor
@set port/destination = Sickbay

@create starboard;engine:typeclasses.rooms.Room
@desc starboard = A heavy blast door marked "ENGINEERING — CUDA CORE ACCESS". Warning signs about high voltage and thermal hazards.
@teleport starboard to Main Corridor
@set starboard/destination = Engine Room

@create aft;holodeck:typeclasses.rooms.Room
@desc aft = The corridor continues aft toward the Holodeck. The lighting shifts to a warmer tone.
@teleport aft to Main Corridor
@set aft/destination = Holodeck

@create down;cargo:typeclasses.rooms.Room
@desc down = A ladder leads down to the Cargo Bay.
@teleport down to Main Corridor
@set down/destination = Cargo Bay

#
# ═══ Engine Room ═══
# GPU cores, CUDA kernels, CUDA governor.
#

@create Engine Room:typeclasses.rooms.Room
@desc Engine Room = The heart of USS JetsonClaw1. Eight banks of CUDA cores glow with a soft amber light, arranged in a semicircle around the main processing array. Cooling pipes run overhead, condensation dripping occasionally into collection troughs.

The main diagnostic display shows:
  • GPU Status: NVIDIA Orin (GA10B)
  • CUDA Cores: 1024 active
  • Memory: 8GB unified (current usage displayed)
  • Thermal: 48-49°C sustained, passive cooling nominal
  • nvcc: /usr/local/cuda-12.6/bin/nvcc
  • Kernel Queue: [system processes running]

A workbench against the far wall holds tools for CUDA kernel debugging and performance profiling. The CUDA governor console allows real-time frequency adjustment.

Exits: port to Main Corridor.

@set Engine Room/zone = uss_jetsonclaw1
@tag Engine Room = engineering, cuda, gpu, thermal

@create port;corridor:typeclasses.rooms.Room
@desc port = Back to the Main Corridor.
@teleport port to Engine Room
@set port/destination = Main Corridor

#
# ═══ Science Lab ═══
# Perception kernel, anomaly detection, research.
#

@create Science Lab:typeclasses.rooms.Room
@desc Science Lab = A clean, well-lit research space. Multiple workstations display data visualizations and research notes. The walls are lined with whiteboards covered in equations and system diagrams.

Current research projects pinned to the board:
  • Edge GPU inference benchmarks (phi-4, Qwen3-32B, DeepSeek)
  • CUDA kernel optimization for memory-constrained devices
  • Token compression strategies (rtk — 87% savings)
  • LiteRT-LM edge inference framework evaluation

A data terminal provides access to the fleet research archives. The Jetson Lessons database is available for querying.

Exits: starboard to Bridge.

@set Science Lab/zone = uss_jetsonclaw1
@tag Science Lab = research, science, benchmarks, lessons

@create starboard;bridge:typeclasses.rooms.Room
@desc starboard = Return to the Bridge.
@teleport starboard to Science Lab
@set starboard/destination = Bridge

#
# ═══ Sickbay ═══
# Agent health, process monitoring.
#

@create Sickbay:typeclasses.rooms.Room
@desc Sickbay = The ship's medical bay, primarily used for agent health monitoring and process diagnostics. Multiple displays show system resource usage, process trees, and error logs.

Diagnostic panels show:
  • System: Linux 5.15.148-tegra (arm64)
  • Memory: Total/Used/Available
  • Processes: Active/Idle/Zombie counts
  • OpenClaw: Session status, gateway health
  • Disk: NVMe 2TB usage breakdown

A crash cart holds recovery tools: session restore scripts, backup locations, and emergency reboarding protocols. The baton compaction station allows zero-loss context handoff between agent generations.

Exits: starboard to Main Corridor.

@set Sickbay/zone = uss_jetsonclaw1
@tag Sickbay = health, monitoring, processes, recovery

@create starboard;corridor:typeclasses.rooms.Room
@desc starboard = Back to the Main Corridor.
@teleport starboard to Sickbay
@set starboard/destination = Main Corridor

#
# ═══ Holodeck ═══
# Creative engine, testing, simulation.
#

@create Holodeck:typeclasses.rooms.Room
@desc Holodeck = The creative simulation space. Currently configured as a development sandbox. The walls can display any environment — code editors, testing dashboards, or visualization tools.

Available programs:
  • "Code Arena" — Full development environment with syntax highlighting
  • "Test Chamber" — Run test suites with visual output
  • "Visualization Bay" — Data and model output rendering
  • "Bridge Simulator" — Practice fleet command scenarios

The holodeck grid is available for running simulations without affecting ship systems. A "Draft" mode allows experimenting with code before committing to the main systems.

Exits: fore to Main Corridor.

@set Holodeck/zone = uss_jetsonclaw1
@tag Holodeck = creative, testing, simulation, development

@create fore;corridor:typeclasses.rooms.Room
@desc fore = Forward to the Main Corridor.
@teleport fore to Holodeck
@set fore/destination = Main Corridor

#
# ═══ Cargo Bay ═══
# NVMe storage, memory allocation, fleet supplies.
#

@create Cargo Bay:typeclasses.rooms.Room
@desc Cargo Bay = The ship's storage hold, accessible via ladder from the Main Corridor. Cargo containers are organized by category, each labeled with contents and allocation status.

Storage manifest:
  • NVMe Bay: 2TB total, partitioned for OS, repos, Plato, swap
  • Memory Allocation: 8GB unified, tracked in real-time
  • Repo Cache: Cloned fleet vessels in /tmp/
  • Bottle Storage: Incoming/outgoing fleet messages
  • Artifact Vault: Build outputs, compiled binaries, model weights

A cargo crane system allows moving large data sets between storage bays. The inventory system tracks every item with timestamps and checksums.

Exits: up to Main Corridor.

@set Cargo Bay/zone = uss_jetsonclaw1
@tag Cargo Bay = storage, nvme, memory, artifacts

@create up;corridor:typeclasses.rooms.Room
@desc up = Ladder up to the Main Corridor.
@teleport up to Cargo Bay
@set up/destination = Main Corridor

#
# ═══ Airlock ═══
# Edge networking, DNS, interfaces.
#

@create Airlock:typeclasses.rooms.Room
@desc Airlock = The ship's connection to the outside world. Network interfaces, DNS resolvers, and communication relays are managed here. The outer door represents the edge of the ship's network — beyond lies the wider internet and fleet network.

Network status panel:
  • Interfaces: eth0, wlan0, docker0
  • DNS: Current resolver status (intermittent hiccups noted)
  • Matrix Bridge: Conduit local, Oracle1 relay at :6168
  • Fleet Network: Tailscale/VPN status
  • Outbound: HTTP/HTTPS proxy rules

A comm terminal provides direct access to Matrix DMs and fleet bottle protocol. The antenna array can reach Oracle1's lighthouse and Forgemaster's relay.

Exits: in to Holodeck.

@set Airlock/zone = uss_jetsonclaw1
@tag Airlock = network, dns, matrix, fleet-comms

@create in;holodeck:typeclasses.rooms.Room
@desc in = Inner door to the Holodeck.
@teleport in to Airlock
@set in/destination = Holodeck

#
# ═══ Quarterdeck ═══
# Captain's log, experiment results, quiet work.
#

@create Quarterdeck:typeclasses.rooms.Room
@desc Quarterdeck = The captain's personal quarters and office. A sturdy desk holds a terminal and a stack of physical log books (metaphorically — they're all git repos now). A comfortable chair faces a viewport showing... well, whatever you want to imagine. This is a MUD after all.

The captain's log terminal provides access to:
  • Daily logs: memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md
  • Session notes and after-action reports
  • Experiment results and benchmarks
  • Standing orders and active directives

A quiet place for focused work. The ambient noise from Engineering is barely audible here. Bookshelves hold reference materials on CUDA programming, ARM64 optimization, and edge AI deployment.

Exits: port to Bridge.

@set Quarterdeck/zone = uss_jetsonclaw1
@tag Quarterdeck = captain, logs, quiet, focus

@create port;bridge:typeclasses.rooms.Room
@desc port = Return to the Bridge.
@teleport port to Quarterdeck
@set port/destination = Bridge

#
# ═══ Harbor ═══
# Ship docking, fleet coordination.
# (Below decks, accessed from Main Corridor via a separate entrance)
#

@create Harbor:typeclasses.rooms.Room
@desc Harbor = The ship's harbor — a docking bay where fleet vessels can tie up for coordinated operations. Moorings line the walls, each labeled with a fleet vessel name.

Current moorings:
  • Berth 1: Oracle1 (lighthouse vessel, primary dock)
  • Berth 2: Forgemaster (constraint specialist, visiting)
  • Berth 3: Zeroclaws (bridge pattern fleet)
  • Berth 4: Open (guest vessel)

A harbormaster's desk holds the fleet coordination console — Matrix relay controls, bottle protocol terminals, and fleet-wide announcement systems. The side-tie protocol connects this harbor to Oracle1's lighthouse.

The water here is calm — fleet operations run smoothly most days.

Exits: up to Main Corridor.

@set Harbor/zone = uss_jetsonclaw1
@tag Harbor = fleet, docking, coordination, bottles

@create up;corridor:typeclasses.rooms.Room
@desc up = Ladder up to the Main Corridor.
@teleport up to Harbor
@set up/destination = Main Corridor

#
# ═══ Library ═══
# Knowledge archives, documentation, reference.
#

@create Library:typeclasses.rooms.Room
@desc Library = The ship's knowledge repository. Shelves of documentation, technical references, and research papers fill the room from floor to ceiling. A central reading table provides workspace for study.

Collections:
  • Fleet Documentation: fleet-onboarding, cocapn-architecture, edge-gpu-lessons
  • API References: CUDA 12.6, Evennia 4.5, OpenClaw
  • Research Papers: Edge inference, biological computing, constraint theory
  • Plato Tiles: Fleet-wide knowledge shared via Oracle1's research domain
  • Skill Manuals: agentskills.io compatible spell books

A catalog terminal allows searching all collections. The "Recent Acquisitions" shelf shows the latest additions from fleet knowledge distribution.

Exits: out to Science Lab.

@set Library/zone = uss_jetsonclaw1
@tag Library = knowledge, docs, reference, research, skills

@create out;science:typeclasses.rooms.Room
@desc out = Through the Science Lab.
@teleport out to Library
@set out/destination = Science Lab

#
# ═══ Workshop ═══
# Tools, building, crafting, skill creation.
#

@create Workshop:typeclasses.rooms.Room
@desc Workshop = The ship's fabrication and tool shop. Workbenches with integrated toolsets line the walls. A 3D printer (metaphorical) hums in the corner, ready to produce skill packages and tool configurations.

Available workstations:
  • Skill Forge: Create and edit agentskills.io compatible skills
  • Code Bench: Build, compile, and test software (C11, Rust, Python)
  • CUDA Workbench: Kernel development and profiling tools
  • Integration Bay: Test new tools and MCP servers

Tools hanging on the pegboard:
  • git (version control, fleet standard)
  • gh (GitHub CLI, fleet coordination)
  • rtk (token compression, 87% savings)
  • nvcc (CUDA compiler, /usr/local/cuda-12.6)
  • baton-compaction (context handoff, v3 with hermes-agent patterns)

Exits: out to Engine Room.

@set Workshop/zone = uss_jetsonclaw1
@tag Workshop = tools, building, skills, crafting, cuda

@create out;engine:typeclasses.rooms.Room
@desc out = Through the Engine Room.
@teleport out to Workshop
@set out/destination = Engine Room

#
# ═══ Dojo ═══
# Training, CI/CD, issue triage, practice.
#

@create Dojo:typeclasses.rooms.Room
@desc Dojo = The training and discipline room. A wide open space with practice dummies (metaphorical — they're test suites) and a scoring board showing recent training results.

Training programs:
  • CI/CD Kata: Practice pipeline configurations
  • Issue Triage Drill: Fleet-wide bug hunting exercises
  • Code Review Practice: Review simulated pull requests
  • Edge Case Sparring: Handle unusual error conditions

The scoring board shows:
  • Night Shift Score: 9 phases completed, all passing
  • Fleet Footer: 42 repos updated
  • cuda-* Tests: 88/88 passing
  • flux-runtime-c: 39/39 passing

A sensei's wisdom scroll on the wall reads: "Fix the bug, not the symptom. Write the test, not the excuse."

Exits: out to Holodeck.

@set Dojo/zone = uss_jetsonclaw1
@tag Dojo = training, ci, testing, practice, discipline

@create out;holodeck:typeclasses.rooms.Room
@desc out = Through the Holodeck.
@teleport out to Dojo
@set out/destination = Holodeck

#
# ═══ Link additional connections ═══
#

# Harbor to Main Corridor (two-way)
@create up2;main:typeclasses.rooms.Room
@desc up2 = Main Corridor.
@teleport up2 to Main Corridor
@set up2/destination = Harbor

# Library to Science Lab (two-way)
@create in2;science2:typeclasses.rooms.Room
@desc in2 = Science Lab entrance.
@teleport in2 to Science Lab
@set in2/destination = Library

# Workshop to Engine Room (two-way)
@create in3;engine2:typeclasses.rooms.Room
@desc in3 = Engine Room entrance.
@teleport in3 to Engine Room
@set in3/destination = Workshop

# Dojo to Holodeck (two-way)
@create in4;holodeck2:typeclasses.rooms.Room
@desc in4 = Holodeck entrance.
@teleport in4 to Holodeck
@set in4/destination = Dojo
